quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  30,1,Alif Lam Mim
  30,2,The Romans have been defeated
  30,3,"in the land nearby, but after their defeat they will themselves be victorious"
  30,4,"in a few years´ time. The affair is Allah´s from beginning to end. On that day, the muminun will rejoice"
  30,5,"in Allah´s help. He grants victory to whoever He wills. He is the Almighty, the Most Merciful"
  30,6,That is Allah´s promise. Allah does not break His promise. But most people do not know it
  30,7,They know an outward aspect of the life of this world but are heedless of the Next World
  30,8,Have they not reflected within themselves? Allah did not create the heavens and the earth and everything between them except with truth and for a fixed term. Yet many people reject the meeting with their Lord
  30,9,Have they not travelled in the earth and seen the final fate of those before them? They had greater strength than them and cultivated the land and inhabited it in far greater numbers than they do. Their Messengers also came to them with the Clear Signs. Allah would never have wronged them; but they wronged themselves
  30,10,Then the final fate of those who did evil will be the Worst because they denied Allah´s Signs and mocked at them
  30,11,"Allah originates creation, then will regenerate it, then you will be returned to Him"
  30,12,On the Day the Hour arrives the evildoers will be in despair
  30,13,None of their partner-gods will intercede for them. They will reject their partner-gods
  30,14,"On the Day the Hour arrives, that Day they will be split up"
  30,15,"As for those who had iman and did right actions, they will be made joyful in a verdant meadow"
  30,16,"But as for those who were kafir and denied Our Signs and the meeting of the Next World, they will be summoned to the punishment"
  30,17,So glory be to Allah when you start the night and when you greet the day
  30,18,"Praise be to Him in the heavens and the earth, in the afternoon and when you reach midday"
  30,19,He brings forth the living from the dead and brings forth the dead from the living and brings the earth to life after it was dead. In the same way you too will be brought forth
  30,20,"Among His Signs is that He created you from dust and here you are now, widespread human beings"
  30,21,Among His Signs is that He created spouses for you of your own kind so that you might find tranquillity in them. And He has placed affection and compassion between you. There are certainly Signs in that for people who reflect
  30,22,Among His Signs is the creation of the heavens and earth and the variety of your languages and colours. There are certainly Signs in that for every being
  30,23,Among His Signs is your sleep by night and day and your seeking after His bounty. There are certainly Signs in that for people who hear
  30,24,"Among His Signs is that He shows you lightning, a source of fear and eager hope, and sends down water from the sky, bringing the dead earth back to life by it. There are certainly Signs in that for people who use their intellect"
  30,25,"Among His Signs is that heaven and earth hold firm by His command. Then, when He calls you forth from the earth, you will emerge at once"
  30,26,Everyone in the heavens and earth belongs to Him. All are submissive to Him
  30,27,"It is He who originated creation and then regenerates it. That is very easy for Him. His is the most exalted designation in the heavens and the earth. He is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  30,28,"He has made an example for you from among yourselves. Are any of the slaves you own partners with you in what We have provided for you so that you are equal in respect of it, you fearing them the same as one another? In that way We make Our Signs clear for people who use their intellect"
  30,29,"However, those who do wrong pursue their whims and desires without any knowledge. Who can guide those whom Allah has led astray? They will have no helpers"
  30,30,"So set your face firmly towards the Deen, as a pure natural believer, Allah´s natural pattern on which He made mankind. There is no changing Allah´s creation. That is the true Deen — but most people do not know it —"